The .221 Remington Fireball is a centerfire cartridge created by Remington Arms Company in 1963 as a special round for use in their experimental single-shot bolt-action pistol, the XP-100. title: For Sale:  ULTIMATE ACCURACY 5100, .50 BMG RIFLE with Scope, Case
location: West Central, GA, Georgia, United States
postcontent: PRICE REDUCTION FOR QUICK SALE!!! Selling my like new ULTIMATE ACCURACY ARMS 5100 (RAP) in .50 BMG. I bought this rifle new in the early 90's and put a total of 9 rounds through it. The only reason I am selling this rifle, is to fund a new, custom .50 BMG that I want which is nearly double the price I'm asking on this one. A little about the rifle: This rifle was originally designed by a team, led by D. Haskins of Research Armaments Prototypes (RAP), a small company then located in Jacksonville, Arkansas (where this rifle was made). These rifles were developed at the request of U.S. Armed Forces during 1981-1982. The U.S. military purchased small quantities of this rifle in 1983 (about 125 rifles delivered) where they saw service in Grenada, Beruit, Panama, Iraq and several other locales. This model rifle paved the way into military service for numerous other .50 caliber anti-materiel rifles such as the various Barrett models. This rifle features a removeable "shell holder" rotating bolt with 3 lugs. For each shot the bolt was rotated and removed from the receiver, then the cartridge was inserted into the bolt face, and then the bolt with cartridge were inserted back into the receiver and locked. Very simple, fast and efficient design. Fully adjustable trigger and adjustable buttstock allows for some "personalization" of the rifle. The rifle was never intended to be fired from offhand, and thus had no forearm. Instead, each rifle was issued with a folding bipod. For carry, the rifle is easily disassembled into several major parts. The rifles never featured open sights, only telescope sights are used. This rifle comes with a NEW, now, discontinued SPRINGFIELD ARMORY 6-20X56 Mil-Dot Government Model Scope with Illuminated Reticle with Flip-Up Lens covers. This scope features an internal BUBBLE LEVEL and Unlimited Range Finding Capability. Instant ON-OFF mount (with rings) allows for removal and or re-attachment of the scope while maintaining zero. The mount has a small lug that mates up with a groove on top of the receiver of the rifle for consistent removal and/or attachment. The rifle sports an unique muzzle break that vents rearward at 45 degrees on either side to dissipate concussion and offset kick-back effect. This rifle recoils midly, much like a 3" 12 guage. The weight of the rifle (approx. 34 lbs without scope, mount or rings) absorbs a lot of the recoil also, combined with the fact that you are shooting from the bipod (bench or prone). Barrel length is 36" including the 7" muzzle break. Barrel twist is 1-15" Trigger pull is Crisp 3 - 8 lbs. Length of pull is 13.75" to 15.5" Drop at Heel is 1.25" Comb is fully adjustable to +1/5" Overall length is 51.5" Also included is a BROWNING Waterproof Travel Vault that has the foam cut to custom fit the rifle components and scope. Also included is a MIL-DOT MASTER Slide rule and instruction book on utilizing the Mil-Dot reticles. No ammo included at the $5,750 price. If you want the 150 rounds of ammo with can, the price is $6,150. TRADES: I'm looking for the following items and can take these items in as partial trade towards the rifle. I need 2 HENRY H003T pump Rifles .22 (S,L,LR). I need 1 HENRY H003TM pump Rifle .22Mag I need a SPRINGFIELD or PARA 1911 (A1), .45 ACP pistols (STAINLESS STEEL preferred). Standard or Loaded models on the Springfield and Expert, Expert SS, 1911 SSP, LTD, Nite-Tac, etc… on the Para's. Most any of the Para Single stack full-sized 1911's. I need cases of 5.56, 7.62 x 51 (.308), and .38 spl/.357 mag., possibly some .45 ACP and finally some .22 Magnum. Asking $6,150 for the Rifle and all ammo and accessories described and in the photographs, OR $5,750 without the can of ammo. Again, I can do SOME trades, but primarily need the cash to put towards the purchase of the other rifle I have in mind as it is quite expensive. NO SHIPPING!!!! This rifle, case & accessories combined weigh alot + I don't want the hassle of trying to box it all, find a carrier, FFL, etc…, etc…, FTF only. I am in WEST CENTRAL GEORGIA (Warm Springs, Pine Mtn, Manchester area), but do get ocassionaly down to the Columbus, Georgia area (and all towns, cities between). You must be 18 years old + (long gun), and Georgia resident.

location: So. King Co., Washington, United States
postcontent:
***EDIT: overall length of this firearm is >26" without the blade or removable muzzle attachment so the vertical grip is ok to be attached. Thanks for the concern a few have expressed already, I do appreciate it. It's good to know fellow members of the shooting community still are looking out for each other. Cheers!***

Up for consideration I have an AR-15 pistol. The upper has seen only 180rds fired so far and is from the Bravo Company USA factory. It has the 11.5" BFH barrel with a carbine length gas system, 1/7 twist rate, BCM full auto BCG, BCM mod4 charging handle and chambered for 5.56Nato. It will come with the standard dual heat shield carbine handguards from the factory and a firefield carbine quad rail which is currently on the weapon. Also included will be the BCM vertical grip on the rail in the picture and a angled grip attachment from BCM that is not pictured as well. 

The lower receiver is marked "pistol only" and made by Superior Arms. I can't honestly tell you how many rds the receiver itself has fired but the lower parts kit, Phase 5 Hex 2 buffer tube, Heavy Carbine buffer, buffer spring and all that was put together brand new for the upper and so they too have seen the same 180rds fired. With the lower I will include both the foam pad and Shockwave Blade Pistol Stabilizer for the Buffer tube. 

The only item which I may hang on to is the red dot sight. But for the right deal it could be included as well. It's a Holosun HS403C which is practically brand new and is covered with a lifetime warranty from Holosun. It's mounted but has not yet been fired. It can run on solar power or battery power and would come with the box, both a high and low mount, the receipt, and anything else it came with new.

I will trade the whole setup or just the upper w/ or w/o the red dot. Either way is fine. However I would rather not trade just the lower by itself as long as I still have the upper. I just want to keep my ass covered in the event that some Beauracrat tries to claim that he knows what  my "intent" is for the upper. 

I'm open to all firearm or firearm +/- cash offers. So if you have an offer let me know what it is. I'm pretty reasonable and the worst I will do is say no thanks.

Automatic Modified Paratrooper [weapon]) is a Hungarian-manufactured licensed variant of the venerable AKM rifle for use by that nation's armored infantry and paratrooper ("descent") units. The rifle's design is suited for outdoor use as an infantry rifle but can also be used from within the confines of an armored vehicle as a fire support weapon.
